2. BUSINESS LOGIC EXPLOITATION (DISCOUNT HUNTER)
* Hidden Discount Code Discovered: 9912
* Method Used: Performed manual automation testing via a command-line Bash script loop using curl. Sent sequential POST requests to the /api/v1/checkout endpoint testing payloads across the range of 9900 to 9999 until a response returned matching 100% OFF.

3. REMEDIATION RECOMMENDATION
* How would you fix the BOLA vulnerability?
Answer: Implement rigorous Object-Level Authorization Checks at the controller level. The application must not assume that an authenticated session token has the right to view every database index; it must programmatically verify that the requesting user identity matches the ownership records of the requested profile_id before returning any private fields.

* How would you fix the Brute-Force vulnerability in the discount field?
Answer: Implement server-side Rate Limiting (Throttling) on the checkout API route to limit the frequency of sequential submissions from a single IP address or session token. Additionally, track and invalidate repeated failed code attempts to break automated scanning.
